Package com.intellij.codeInspection.reference

Interface RefMethod

  • All Superinterfaces:
    RefElement, RefEntity, RefJavaElement, UserDataHolder
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    RefImplicitConstructor
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    RefImplicitConstructorImpl, RefMethodImpl

    public interface RefMethod
extends RefJavaElement
    A node in the reference graph corresponding to a Java method.

      • getReturnValueIfSame

        java.lang.String getReturnValueIfSame()
        If the method always returns the same value, returns that value (the name of a static final field or the text of a literal expression). Otherwise, returns null.
        Returns:
        the method return value or null if it's different or impossible to determine.

      • getUnThrownExceptions

        PsiClass [] getUnThrownExceptions()
        Returns the list of exceptions which are included in the throws list of the method but cannot be actually thrown. To return valid results, requires com.intellij.codeInspection.unneededThrows.RedundantThrowsGraphAnnotator. (Dbl) Annotator registration is possible in InspectionProfileEntry.initialize(com.intellij.codeInspection.GlobalInspectionContext) or GlobalInspectionTool.getAnnotator(RefManager)
        Returns:
        the list of exceptions declared but not thrown, or null if there are no such exceptions.
